{"word":"ἀκολουθέω","slug":"ἀκολουθέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἀϰολουϑέω</el></b> [<el>ἀ-</el><a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ copul.\">copul.</a>, <el>ϰέλευϑος</el> ‘road, path’]<b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp></b> ‘to be in motion in sequence behind someone’ <b><i>follow</i> <a href='B:470 21:9'>Mt 21:9</a></b> (here <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ opp.\">opp.</a> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:προάγω\">προάγω</a></el>); more generally, of a crowd keeping up with Jesus<b> <a href='B:470 4:25'>4:25</a>; <a href='B:490 7:9'>Lk 7:9</a>; <a href='B:500 6:2'>J 6:2</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp></b> ‘to be in close association with someone’, <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ esp.\">esp.</a> as a disciple<b> <a href='B:470 9:9'>Mt 9:9</a>; <a href='B:480 1:18'>Mk 1:18</a>; <a href='B:490 5:11'>Lk 5:11</a>.</b> Of happening in sequence <b><a href='B:480 16:17'>Mk 16:17</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ v.l.\">v.l.</a></b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀκοή\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀκουσθεῖσι\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}